      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "Toronto's bats erupted like a spring storm over Fenway, pounding the Red Sox into submission with back-to-back triumphs that snapped a skid and ignited faint hopes in the AL East scrum. <strong>Ernie Clement's two-run homer and Brandon Valenzuela's solo blast fueled Wednesday's 8-1 rout</strong>, capping a three-of-four series haul against Boston while Spencer Miles locked the door with a clutch strikeout of Roman Anthony. At 14-16, fourth place and 5.5 games back, the Blue Jays cling to wild-card dreams on a two-game heater - no fireworks yet, but the trajectory bends upward if the momentum holds. Clement's power surge has been the spark, turning mid-order meh into menace, though the bullpen's late-season reliability remains a nagging question mark. No fresh injuries clouding the clubhouse, just a roster hungry to build. <strong>Tonight's road test at Minnesota pits them against Bailey Ober at 6:40 PM ET - win here, and the hunt feels real; stumble, and it's back to the pack.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 30, 2026"
      },
